* The May Fourth Movement (1919) protested against the Treaty of Versailles and foreign domination, setting the stage for future anti-colonial movements across Asia.
* The Great Leap Forward (1958-1961) aimed to rapidly industrialize and modernize China, but led to widespread famine and suffering, killing an estimated 45 million people.
